Events.title: Jonita Gandhi Live Concert
Events.description:
Jonita Gandhi, the acclaimed Indian-Canadian playback singer, exudes an extraordinary blend of versatility and musical finesse that distinguishes her in the realm of music. With a rich foundation in Hindustani classical music, Jonita`s artistic journey flourished through her captivating YouTube cover songs, resonating with a diverse global audience. Collaborating with eminent music directors such as A.R. Rahman and Pritam, she has graced the Bollywood landscape with awe-inspiring performances in chart-topping hits like "Arabic Kuthu" from "Beast" and "The Breakup Song" from "Ae Dil Hai Mushkil". Jonita`s seamless transition across genres, coupled with her profound ability to evoke profound emotions through her ethereal vocals, has solidified her position as a revered and celebrated figure in the music industry.



Catch Jonita Gandhi performing live on 22nd July 2023 at Hitex Exhibition Grounds, Hyderabad.

Definitely come with your entire family if you don`t have any fear of disownment.

Events.title: Gaurav Gupta Live Event
Events.description:
Gaurav Gupta is a baniya who is extravagant when it comes to delivering jokes, he is a dentist by profession and a comic by recession, his comedy involves keen observations of daily life, people and funny encounters with them, he has won several open mic competitions like 94.3 FM Radio One LOL contest, Piano Man Tongue in Cheek in Delhi and Chalta Hai Comedy in Mumbai and has performed at Canvas Laugh Club, Mumbai and Delhi. He has also performed at theatre shows in Delhi like Akshara, Alliance Francaise, Lok Kala Manch and so on. He has been performing for prestigious Best in Stand-up Comedy Show at Canvas Laugh Club, Gurgaon cyber hub. 







He is a recent WhatsApp viral sensation across India and abroad for his video Being Baniya which received millions of hits on Facebook and Youtube. Gaurav has done corporate shows for many reputed corporate clients like Fitbit, Kotak Mahindra Bank, MRF tires, SBI, Valvoline oil, Mother diary, UHG healthcare and so many. Also, he was among the top 12 finalists of a TV show Great Indian Laughter Challenge on Star Plus judged by Bollywood actor Akshay Kumar so get ready to have your full 32 out with his deadly combination of comedy and dentist skills.
